attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, not stripped

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a Linux DDoS (Distributed Denial of Service) bot, likely a variant of the Gafgyt (Bashlite) or Mirai families. It backgrounds itself via fork, connects to a hardcoded C2 server ('OreoServer'), and implements an extensive suite of attack vectors including HTTP, TCP, UDP, VSE, SSDP, and NTP floods. It features specialized modules ('SendOVH', 'SendNUKE', 'SendZAP') containing hardcoded attack payloads and can execute arbitrary shell commands via fdpopen. It also attempts to prevent system reboots by interacting with /dev/watchdog and masks its process name using prctl.
